title: Re: Dukeburgerliciously dukeburgerific
content:
"Whos walter? Is it just some joke/cameo you added in, or has he just not been in any episode yet?"
As far as I know Walter is some scientist dude from ThisStrife's comics that are built in Build.. The Walter graphics there are from Half-Life I think. Not 100% sure.

"And is that "chew gum and I'm all out of gum" thing a Duke Nukem thing, or is it from something else that I've never noticed/seen."
Hehe, it's one well-known Duke one-liner. [img]http://www.classicgaming.com/cc314/msgboard/emotikeen-lol.gif[/img] Duke says that in the very first level (Raw Meat) of episode Shrapnel City (in Duke Nukem 3D), once you start the level.3D Realms: "Do you think there'll ever be a sequel to your game(s)?"
Tom Hall: "If I owned Keen, there sure would be. I don't consider that GBA game canon by any means."

title: Re: Dukeburgerliciously dukeburgerific
content:
Walter is a scientist from Half-Life who has also appeared in many "This Strife" comics.

The "kick ass / chew gum" phrase is a Duke one-liner that is actually STOLEN from a movie. Some horror movie about zombies, I think. [img]http://www.classicgaming.com/cc314/msgboard/emotikeen-halloween.gif[/img] [img]http://www.classicgaming.com/cc314/msgboard/emotikeen-bloody.gif[/img]

Watch Keen's eyes when Lindsey gasps in melodramatic horror. Follow his gaze.
